How to create a ssh key for github

1 - Check if there are already any ssh keys
ls ~./ssh

2 - If there is no keys created, create one:
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "email associated"

3 - Make sure the key added to the agent
eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

4 - Check if the key was added
ssh-add -l

5 - Test with explicit key
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 git@github

If it works you should see:
Hi username! You've successfully authenticated, but GitHub does not provide shell access.

6 - Another test
ssh -T git@github.com

or create a config file to avoid conflits with another keys
nano ~/.ssh/config
Host github-personal
    HostName github.com
    User git
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

And then
ssh -T github-personal

7 - Copy the public key content id_ed25519.pub to the new ssh key created in github
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub

